originalText.text: I lost my eyebrows at 23 and they never grew back. For the past years I had to spend time every day drawing them on or touching them up and worrying they wouldnt smudge off. Rhondi not only made the proper corrections from a very old mistake another tattooer made, she took the time to really find my perfect shape and color. She also cares so much about each patient, she came up with a plan to tattoo powder brows as a base since there was no eyebrow hair, and after healing go back in with a separate color to micro-blade over with. We did the first step today and it already looks INCREDIBLE. It looks phenomenal even without the microblade, but I‚Äôm sure they‚Äôre going to somehow look even more incredible after. I will leave pictures once the whole process has healed!! If youre looking for a phenomenal artist she is it!!!!!

originalText.text: I was living with these unsightly scars on my face and shoulder from a car accident. Rhondi did an incredible job camouflaging my scars with permanent makeup.  She is a true artist and was able to naturally erase the scars.  It was an incredible experience with amazing results.  I really appreciate the work Rhondi does and I plan to go back for more permanent makeup applications.

originalText.text: I rarely take time to post a review unless I am completely "WOWED" by a service received where I feel it important to share that experience with others. I have been going to Cateyz Lash Studio for years and the only time I stopped was during Covid when it was closed due to compliance with NJ regulations. I had been on the fence for years on what to do with my crazy shaped eyebrows which continued to decline over the years. They were causing me huge amounts of time to fix each day when getting ready and doing my makeup. I realized that the same reasons that I started with my eyelashes to reduce the time spent in my busy life was a similar driving force to do the permanent make-up.  Even though I have been a long term client, Rhondi treated me with the upmost care from beginning to end to ensure my entire experience was nothing but the best. She went through a complete consultation to discuss what I was trying to achieve and to come up with a design and plan that I felt comfortable with knowing it would feel like a big change to my facial appearance. The same way I trusted her to my eyelashes I gave her complete reign to use her expertise to transform me. She uses the latest equipment and high end products which made me feel comfortable that they were not cheap materials that I would be allergic to. After the procedure was completed; I was nervous to look in the mirror and was so happy with the results. It is a big change so you need to be prepared if you have gone years of putting your own "on". It was love at first site and I knew that we would get to that happy place even though they appeared dark. You need to take care of all of the instructions given for 2 weeks and then when after the perfect time of healing, she gave me the final tweak of a 2nd round to make them PERFECT.  I did NOT want the over the top microblade look and elected for a defined powder fill in. My style and appropriate for my lifestyle. Rhondi is an artist and I strongly recommend her.
